 lawmakers in Colorado and Washington are considering spelling out what 's allowed when it comes to making the concentrated marijuana at home .
The proposals came after an increase in home fires and blasts linked to homemade hash oil .
In Colorado , at least 30 people were injured last year in 32 butane explosions involving hash oil -- nearly three times the number .
Washington 's legal marijuana law in 2012 did not permit the production of hash or edibles .